Creating the Map for Geographic Profit Margin 12

Area Layer

Go to charts and drag Map to the sheet. Resize the Map and rename it ‘Geographic Profit Margin’.

Click on Add Layer on the right side of the screen and select Area layer.

Click on add dimension and select Map hierarchy. Click on Location and select Map Hierarchy under Location field. Make sure that scope for location is on and showing Auto

Click on colors and turn off auto colors and select by expression.

Download the attached file to copy and paste the color expression under expression.

Check the box that says ‘The expression is a color code’

Go to Options and click on General to select None under show legend. Turn on show label and show in zoom levels

Click on Layer display and check Show layer. Turn on show in zoom levels and turn off Visible drill-down levels then select Country and State.

 

Point Layer

Go back to Data and add a point layer and use map hierarchy as the dimension.

Click on Location and make sure that Map hierarchy is selected under Location field.

Turn off Scope for location and select City, Place under location type. Select Country under country and State under Administrative area (level 1)

Click on Size and shape and size it by Sales. Turn of the master measure formatting to adjust the bubble size and select bubble under shape

Click on colors and turn off auto colors and select by expression.

Use the same color expression you used in the area layer and paste the color expression under expression.

Check the box that says ‘The expression is a color code’

Go to Options and click on General to select None under show legend. Turn off show label

Click on Layer display and check Show layer. Turn on show in zoom levels and turn off Visible drill-down levels then select City

Click on appearance and turn off legend under presentation
